.Dd $Mdocdate: June 28 2026 $
.Dt SLAC 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm slac
.Nd spam limiting and classification mail delivery agent
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl d
.Op Fl c Ar file
.Op Cm mda | web | tui
.Nm
.Op Fl c Ar file
.Cm list
.Fl -mailbox Cm inbox | spam
.Nm
.Op Fl c Ar file
.Cm show
.Fl -mailbox Cm inbox | spam
.Fl -id Ar number
.Nm
.Op Fl c Ar file
.Cm move
.Fl -mailbox Cm inbox | spam
.Fl -id Ar number
.Fl -to Cm inbox | spam
.Op Fl -reason Ar text
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a local mail delivery agent for
.Xr smtpd 8 .
It reads one message from standard input,
classifies the message using an OpenAI-compatible chat completions endpoint,
adds
.Ql X-SLAC-*
headers when configured to do so,
and then either delegates normal delivery to
.Xr mail.local 8
or appends the message to a quarantine mbox.
.Pp
When invoked without a command,
.Nm
runs in
.Cm mda
mode.
This is the mode intended for use from an
.Ic mda
action in
.Xr smtpd.conf 5 .
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl c Ar file , Fl -config Ar file
Read configuration from
.Ar file .
Without this option,
.Nm
searches
.Pa ~/.config/slac/slac.toml
and then
.Pa /etc/slac.toml .
If no configuration file is found, built-in defaults are used.
.It Fl d , Fl -debug
Also log diagnostic messages to standard error.
This is useful when running
.Nm
by hand with a saved message.
.It Fl h , Fl -help
Display usage information and exit.
.El
.Pp
The commands are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm mda
Read a message from standard input and process it for delivery.
The message is normally delivered by the command configured in
.Xr slac.toml 5 .
If quarantine is enabled and the classifier result meets the configured
threshold and verdict policy,
the message is appended to the configured spam mbox instead.
.Pp
Classifier, configuration, and quarantine failures are fail-open in MDA mode:
.Nm
logs the error and attempts normal delivery so that mail is not lost.
.It Cm web
Reserved for a future web interface.
The command is accepted but currently exits unsuccessfully.
.It Cm tui
Open an interactive terminal interface for reviewing the user's inbox and
spam mbox.
.It Cm list Fl -mailbox Cm inbox | spam
List message summaries from a logical mailbox as tab-separated output.
The
.Cm inbox
mailbox is
.Pa /var/mail/$USER
or
.Pa /var/mail/$LOGNAME .
The
.Cm spam
mailbox is the configured quarantine path.
The printed message IDs are scan indexes and should be used immediately.
.It Cm show Fl -mailbox Cm inbox | spam Fl -id Ar number
Write the selected message to standard output.
.It Xo
.Cm move
.Fl -mailbox Cm inbox | spam
.Fl -id Ar number
.Fl -to Cm inbox | spam
.Op Fl -reason Ar text
.Xc
Move the selected message between the inbox and spam mbox.
The destination copy receives correction headers and a correction record is
written under
.Pa ~/.local/share/slac .
Moving from
.Cm spam
to
.Cm inbox
records a corrected verdict of
.Dq ham .
Moving from
.Cm inbox
to
.Cm spam
records a corrected verdict of
.Dq spam .
.El
.Sh MDA OPERATION
In
.Cm mda
mode,
.Nm
builds a bounded prompt from the message and the configured rules,
sends it to the configured chat completions endpoint,
and expects a JSON classification containing
.Va spam_probability ,
.Va verdict ,
and
.Va reasons .
The verdict is one of
.Dq spam ,
.Dq ham ,
or
.Dq unsure .
.Pp
If
.Ic classification.add_headers
is true,
.Nm
adds headers such as:
.Pp
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
.Ql X-SLAC-Status
.It
.Ql X-SLAC-Action
.It
.Ql X-SLAC-Verdict
.It
.Ql X-SLAC-Spam-Probability
.It
.Ql X-SLAC-Spam-Threshold
.It
.Ql X-SLAC-Reasons
.El
.Pp
If classification fails and header insertion is enabled,
.Nm
adds
.Ql X-SLAC-Status: classifier-error
and delivers normally.
.Pp
Quarantine is considered only when
.Ic classification.observe_only
is false.
The message must have a spam probability greater than or equal to
.Ic classification.spam_threshold
and the verdict must match
.Ic quarantine.require_verdict .
.Sh REVIEW INTERFACE
The
.Cm tui
command displays inbox and spam mbox summaries with a detail pane.
The following keys are supported:
.Bl -tag -width PageDown -compact
.It Ic Tab
Switch between inbox and spam.
.It Ic Up , Ic Down , Ic j , Ic k
Move the selection.
.It Ic PageUp , Ic PageDown
Move by a page or scroll the preview.
.It Ic Enter
Open the selected message preview.
.It Ic m
Move the selected message to the other mailbox.
.It Ic r
Refresh mailbox contents.
.It Ic q
Quit, or close the preview.
.It Ic Esc
Cancel a move reason prompt.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "~/.local/share/slac/corrections/messages/" -compact
.It Pa /etc/slac.toml
System configuration file.
.It Pa ~/.config/slac/slac.toml
Per-user configuration file.
.It Pa /var/mail/$USER
Default inbox inspected by review commands.
.It Pa ~/spam
Default quarantine mbox.
.It Pa ~/.local/share/slac/corrections.jsonl
Correction history used for bounded classifier feedback.
.It Pa ~/.local/share/slac/corrections/messages/
Corrected message snapshots named by SHA-256 digest.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std slac
.Pp
Command-line usage errors exit with
.Dv EX_USAGE .
Operational failures exit with
.Dv EX_TEMPFAIL .
.Sh EXAMPLES
Classify and deliver a saved message using an explicit configuration:
.Pp
.Dl $ slac -d -c /etc/slac.toml mda < message.eml
.Pp
Configure
.Xr smtpd 8
to use
.Nm
for local delivery:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
action "local_slac" mda "/usr/local/bin/slac -c /etc/slac.toml mda" alias <aliases>
match for local action "local_slac"
.Ed
.Pp
Validate and reload
.Xr smtpd 8
after editing
.Pa /etc/mail/smtpd.conf :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
# smtpd -n
# rcctl reload smtpd
.Ed
.Pp
Start in observe-only mode in
.Xr slac.toml 5 ,
then inspect delivered messages for
.Ql X-SLAC-*
headers.
After the classifier behavior is acceptable,
disable observe-only mode and use a conservative spam threshold.
.Pp
Review quarantined mail:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ slac -c /etc/slac.toml list --mailbox spam
$ slac -c /etc/slac.toml show --mailbox spam --id 0
$ slac -c /etc/slac.toml move --mailbox spam --id 0 --to inbox \e
    --reason "false positive"
.Ed
.Pp
Open the interactive review interface:
.Pp
.Dl $ slac -c /etc/slac.toml tui
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr slac.toml 5 ,
.Xr smtpd.conf 5 ,
.Xr mail.local 8 ,
.Xr smtpd 8
.Sh AUTHORS
.An Mike Larkin Aq Mt mlarkin@nested.page
